  "title": "Humic Acid (HA) and Fulvic Acid (FA) Carbon",
  "abstract": "Humic acid (HA) and fulvic acid (FA), key passive fractions of soil organic matter, differ in molecular size and solubility, contributing to long-term carbon sequestration and nutrient exchange, and are extracted using base–acid fractionation. Their characterization provides insights into soil quality, carbon stability, and nutrient availability.",
